      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable that you are concerned about unnecessary medication and potential side effects. However, self-monitoring and resuming antibiotics only when symptoms return is not the recommended medical practice for stopping an antibiotic course. The goal of the full prescription is to eliminate all microbial colonies to prevent relapse, which is a much more serious risk than completing the prescribed course. Please discuss your concerns about the length of the prescription with your prescribing physician so they can address your specific worries.",
      "source": "target",
